As for AoE groups, they're rare now. Why? It aint worth it anymore, it's more dangerous and take more time to make XP now since the nerfs, unless we go to some very specific places where we end up having half the zone against us cuz we take 2-3 camps (like Seb, which is now dangerous to AoE because of the new spell abilities of NPCs, another AoE nerf if nothing else). Acrylia WAS a fun way of doing it. WAS is the magic word here. AoE WAS fun. Now, it's either too dangerous, or the place is filled with groups and if we start AoEing, we get bitched at.<br>
<br>
When we talk about damage/mana per spell DD yeah, we are the best, but that's all we have. You Gamrok, you're lom and you're medding, no problem, the pet is still hacking away. Heck, just your pet will deal at least close to the ammount of damage I deal in a fight in an XP group.<br>
<br>
As for running out of mana too quickly on big fights, how the hell could I rethink my strategy? Me waiting 30 sec between each nukes, or sending them all closer together (as long as I dont draw aggro) doesnt change a goddamn thing. I still deal the same crappy ammount of damage and spend the same ammount of thing doing nothing but standing there looking at the thing. Not like I have that many options. <p><center>
