<br>
I know how you feel, I used to feel the same way about mages.. Then I opened up my eyes, and I saw how useful I really was.  <br>
<br>
First of all, you need to think outside of the box.  Fine, you don't want to solo.  Ok, you don't want to AE.  Well, you can either join a melee centric group and feel out of place, or you can do something different.  If mana is a problem for you try grouping with a mage and a cleric/shaman that doesn't mind paying attention for the entire night.  You will never run out of mana because of mod rods, you'll have a tank, you'll have damage and you'll have a healer, and if you aren't happy with root crowd control you can add an enchanter in there for KEI as well, or a bard for manasong.<br>
<br>
Wizards can have insane mana regen, with familiar, epic, some mental clarity and easy to get FT items you could easily reach about 15ish mana regen, add that to harvest and I really don't see why you need more.  Sure, you can't regen as fast as some other classes, but if you were to team up with those classes you could supplement each other's strengths and weaknesses to make a pretty good team.  For example, a mage and a wizard could in essence duo almost any non-summoning mob if the wizard is properly equipped (flux staff) without using a single bit of mana, in fact with that sissy sword pet wizards get I'm sure you could do the same with minor mana usage.  Back to the mage/wizard duo, add in actually using mana, and combining wizard epic with mod rods and you've got a pretty good killing team, maybe not as good as soloing but it's more fun.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr> You Gamrok, you're lom and you're medding, no problem, the pet is still hacking away. Heck, just your pet will deal at least close to the ammount of damage I deal in a fight in an XP group.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
Mages are pretty overpowered in all situations.  We can make or break a raid and with a healer in the group we can always have enough mana to nuke to our heart's content while still keeping the group constantly pulling and killing mobs.  So, what do wizard's do?  The same things as rogues.  A shaman and a mage can pull almost non-stop in almost any exp situation, but that doesn't necessarily mean it'll be good exp.  Toss in a few monks, wizards and rogues and suddenly you've got a killing machine.  <br>
<br>
So, what exactly do wizards bring to a group?  Well for one thing, they bring damage.  1.4k damage on mobs with 6k health isn't so bad when there's 6 people in the group.  On top of that you can burn down mobs in an emergency, evac in an emergency, your crowd control is better than any other non-mezzing class with root and flux stuff, and you can snare.  But wait! If I want snare, evac, root and damage I can just go to a druid and get dots and heals on top of all that.  Newsflash:  Wizards outdamage druids, and damage = exp.<br>
<br>
Anyways, I'm not gonna bother responding to the other thread since it's going to end up in the same way..  And I really should be studying, just keep your eyes open and you'll see how useful wizards are.  I know you aren't going to change your opinion from reading other's posts, because I didn't either. <p><FONT Face="Arial" size="-1">
